Welcome! I’m going to introduce you to two identities in my life. These two paths will end up in the same result. So, which one do I want to go down in? width="700px" height="375px" /> [[Middle School]]I’m pretty sure nobody wants to relive their middle school experience. We can all agree that we did some embarrassing things. I personally made listening to Panic! at the Disco a personality trait. (Did not age well.) Other than that, you also met some more of your best friends. I also faced my first sprinkle of racism. Remember that Omari kid in seventh grade math in fourth period? The one that was friends with Olivia G. Yeah him. Despite him being kinda chill, him calling me Chen (which is a typical Chinese last name) was not cool. It took Olivia to speak up about it and I constantly thank her for that. I was too scared to speak up and it’s fine. Only if I had enough power to speak up. [[High School]]Ah the four years of hell. I've experienced my first heartbreak and my first and only high school dance (both connecting to each other). Made more friends. Went to New York with three of my friends during spring break of freshman year. Coming home late at night during the fall semester of sophomore year because of football games and marching band competitions. Going to Denny’s with the band and seeing a rat come out of one of the booth seats. One thing you didn’t expect was spending the last half of your junior year and senior year at home doing online school. It’s all because of a thing called COVID-19. <style> img{ max-width:100%; max-height:100% } </style> <img src= "https://alicia-huynh.github.io/images/lastdayofmb.jpg" width="640px" height="311px" > [[The Pandemic]]I went to Marina Supermarket with my dad to get some Vietnamese meatloaf for my family and the only thing that I was worried about was people getting close to me and/or seeing people without a mask on. The one thing that I wasn’t prepared for was being called a slur. That slur started with a ‘g’ and if you’re a fan of David So, it’s the title of his movie. During this whole pandemic the rise of hate crimes against Asian Americans have risen ever since the pandemic started. [[Asian Hate Crimes]] [[Someone Else's Expreience]](link:"2020")[(gotoURL:"https://stopaapihate.org/")]- Hate crimes against people of Asian descent have risen by 76% (according to republished FBI data). (link:"2021")[(gotoURL:"http://aapidata.com/blog/tip-iceberg-march2021-survey/")]- 10% of Asian Americans and Native Hawaiian/Pacific Islanders have experienced hate crimes/incidents. 1 out of 4 AAPIs are affected by it overall. 2012- 1 out of every 10 are affected so far. <style> img{ max-width:100%; max-height:100% } </style> <img src="http://aapidata.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aapi-experiences-over-time-1024x768.png" width="512px" height="384px"> [[What You Can Do]]Hear those out that are affected. Listen to their story/struggles. Sign petitions Spread awareness Join protests (Scan the QR for protests in the Bay) Don’t victim shame, hear the victim out Don’t say any microaggressions against them. NO MEANS NO!!! <style> img{ max-width:100%; max-height:100% } </style> <img src= "https://alicia-huynh.github.io/images/protest_qr.png" width="150px" height="186px"> *Some people allowed me to use their name in their experience and some did not* [[Asian Personal Experience]] [[Female Personal Experience]]My whole life I’ve identified as a female. I’ve identified with the assigned gender that I was born with. Ever since I was a little kid, I knew that I was a female. As I got older, I didn’t know about the challenges I would be faced with. <style> img{ max-width:100%; max-height:100% } </style> <img src= "https://alicia-huynh.github.io/images/graduation_pic.JPG" width="750px" height="500px" > [[Inscurities]]Fifth grade was the first time where I got bullied. Long story short, a girl called me fat and pregnant while we were waiting in the lunch line. My parents got hold of it and comforted me for a little while. Ever since that day, I started to feel insecure about myself and my body. [[So Many Standards]]Like I said, I’m an Asian American woman. I ‘have’ to fit into the American and Asian standards. Typical American standards such as being a size two, completely shaved (not including hair), and constantly wearing makeup. Asian standards are almost the and adding the pale skin aspect. [[Familial Standards]]I’m an only child in my immediate family and I’m the first female grandchild in my extended family. I have pretty high standards in my family. I have to take care of them first of all. Second of all, I have to fit into the conservative view that my family has even though I still don’t. Standards such as the typical female stereotype. It’s a woman’s job to cook even though it’s a basic life skill. I have to follow either one of my grandmother’s footsteps by becoming a pharmacist or a lawyer. Having a conservative political view. Look skinny and wear makeup so “boys will like me.” [[Someone's Familial Experience]] [[A Woman’s Role in Life]]Ever since I was growing up, I’ve been told that a woman’s role in life is to get married, have kids, and take care of them while having a full time job at the same time. I’m sure any female can relate to this. It wasn’t until I got older I started to realize that I have more of a purpose in life than what I was told growing up. I mean I do want to have kids and get married but I also want to do more than that. <style> img{ max-width:100%; max-height:100% } </style> <img src="https://www.insuranceandestates.com/wp-content/uploads/life-insurance-for-women-300x191.jpg" > [[Stats]]//''Trigger Warning''// This next path will be talking about sexual assult. If you get easily triggered by it, then you can move to the “What You Can Do Section.” [[SA Stats]] [[What You Can Do]] ''Sexual Assault''- sexual contact or behavior that occurs without explicit consent of the victim. 3.8+ million women are currently living on Earth. In their lifetime 1 in 3, around 736 million, will experience getting sexually assaulted. Mind you, this is when the victim reports the case. If you were on TikTok around mid-March, you might’ve heard of the stat 97%. This started when the case of Sarah Everard from the UK who was kidnapped, raped, and mudered by an officer. After that story came out, the stat of 97% came out saying that women in the ages between 18-24 in the UK have been sexually harrassed. <style> img{ max-width:100%; max-height:100% } </style> <img src="https://cdn.statcdn.com/Infographic/images/normal/11596.jpeg" width="300px" height="300px" > [[The 97% Trend]]This sparked outrage on TikTok and victims of sexual harassment/assault have came out with their stories. While looking through the comments in the video, most of them were positive and everyone was empowering each other. While there was some empowerment, there was also some backlash. There were some men who started the #NotAllMen movement. It’s basically men saying that not all men are like this. We know but we don’t know who doesn’t act like that. That’s why we say “Not All Men." <style> img{ max-width:100%; max-height:100% } </style> <img src= "https://media.distractify.com/brand-img/-ts4dr-C9/480x252/what-is-the-97-percent-tiktok-1616025817637.jpg" > [[What You Can Do]]Chose one of these stories to start on. [[Jack's Experience]] [[PR Major's Experience]] [[Bio-Med's Experience]][[Bio-Med Experience]] [[Charlize's Experience]] [[J's Expreience]]November 6, 2003, the day that I was born. Born in O’Connor Hospital and to two amazing parents who immigrated from Vietnam. I was stopped at a red light once and this car of young, white men, (probably college dudes) rolled down their window, called me a terrorist, threw their soda can at me, and then drove off." <img src="http://www.religious-symbols.net/Pictures/sikh-symbols_1.png" > [[Asian Hate Crimes]] Age- 22 Year- 4th Major- Molecular Biology "People are judgmental of appearances, always. You have to carry yourself a certain way. There are generally so many more beauty standards and expectations from women than men. My grandma always talks about how I should lose weight or do makeup, etc or else I won't get married." [[A Woman’s Role in Life]] Age- 18 Year- 1st Major- Biomedical Engineering "Sexism/people believing I'm unable to do something seen as traditionally masculine, as well as some harassment." [[Female Personal Experience]] [[Welcome Page]] Name- Jack Liu Age- 19 Year- 3rd Major- Software Engineering "When I was young, some kid simply didn't respect me and saw me as an outsider" [[Asian Personal Experience]] [[Welcome Page]] Name- Charlize Inong Age- 18 Year- 1st Major- Business with Concentration in Marketing "I have been catcalled, body shamed, and sexualized through dance or just casually walking outside in my pajamas.} [[Female Personal Experience]] [[Welcome Page]] Age- 19 Year- 2nd Major- Public Relations "Since I lived in the Bay Area and it’s very diverse, I have never personally experienced racism as an Asian American. However there are micro aggressions like people asking where I’m “really from” even though I was born in America. Also with the pandemic, more Asian hate and racism has risen." [[Asian Personal Experience]] [[Welcome Page]] Age- 18 Year- 1st Major- Biomedical Enginnering "Here and there. Mostly just jabs about being a taxi driver, people looking at me intensely when Tunak Tunak Tun plays, and on the slightest occasions people backing or walking away from me if I am dressed in specific ways." [[Asian Personal Experience]] [[Welcome Page]] Age- 18 Year- 1st Major- Undeclared "As a female it is a hard life with being treated differently just based for that reason but at the same time I feel I can be really confident with myself and have the courage to do what many boys can do." [[Female Personal Experience]] [[Welcome Page]] When the pandemic started, I thought it would only last two weeks. Those two weeks turned into a month, and that month turned into many. During those months, cooped up in my house, I wanted to get out. That happened when the restrictions were lifted up a little during the summer. While being cooped up in the house and outside, I fully got to see the racism. <style> img{ max-width:100%; max-height:100% } </style> <img src= "https://alicia-huynh.github.io/images/dad_bbq.jpg" width="387px" height="516px" > [[What I Experienced]]
